    "solution": "**วิธีการ:** Integration by Parts ซ้ำ\n**รอบที่ 1:** ให้ $u=x^{2}$, $dv=e^{1x}dx$\n• $du=2x^{1}dx$\n• $v=\\dfrac{e^{1x}}{1}$\n$\\displaystyle\\int x^{2}e^{1x}dx=\\dfrac{x^{2}e^{1x}}{1}-\\dfrac{2}{1}\\int x^{1}e^{1x}dx$\n**รอบที่ 2:** ให้ $u=x^{1}$, $dv=e^{1x}dx$\n• $du=1x^{0}dx$ (=$dx$)\n• $v=\\dfrac{e^{1x}}{1}$\n$\\displaystyle\\int x^{1}e^{1x}dx=\\dfrac{x^{1}e^{1x}}{1}-\\dfrac{1}{1}\\int x^{0}e^{1x}dx$\n**รวมผลลัพธ์:**\n$=$\\dfrac{e^{1x}}{1^3}(1^2x^2-2x+2)+C$$\n\n✅ คำตอบ: $\\dfrac{e^{1x}}{1^3}(1^2x^2-2x+2)+C$"
